nodes.name: executeRuling

params._descriptionEncryptedLink: Time after which a party can automatically execute the arbitrable transaction.
params._timeoutLocked: Timeout after which the finder can call the function `executePayment`.

appeal(bytes32).details: Appeal an appealable ruling. Transfer the funds to the arbitrator. Note that no checks are required as the checks are done by the arbitrator.

changeAddressAndDescriptionEncrypted(byt.details: Change the address used to encrypt the description link and the description.

params._addressForEncryption: Time after which a party can automatically execute the arbitrable transaction.

changeRewardAmount(bytes32,uint256).details: Change the reward amount of the good.

params._rewardAmount: The amount of the reward for the good.

changeTimeoutLocked(bytes32,uint256).details: Change the reward amount of the good.

params._timeoutLocked: Timeout after which the finder can call the function `executePayment`.

params._descriptionLink: The link to the description of the good (optionnal).

executeTransaction(bytes32).details: Transfer the transaction's amount to the finder if the timeout has passed.

pay(bytes32,uint256).details: Pay finder. To be called if the good has been returned.

payArbitrationFeeByFinder(bytes32).details: Pay the arbitration fee to raise a dispute. To be called by the finder. UNTRUSTED. Note that this function mirrors payArbitrationFeeByFinder.

payArbitrationFeeByOwner(bytes32).details: Pay the arbitration fee to raise a dispute. To be called by the owner. UNTRUSTED. Note that the arbitrator can have createDispute throw, which will make this function throw and therefore lead to a party being timed-out. This is not a vulnerability as the arbitrator can rule in favor of one party anyway.

reimburse(bytes32,uint256).details: Reimburse owner of the good. To be called if the good can't be fully returned.

rule(uint256,uint256).details: Give a ruling for a dispute. Must be called by the arbitrator. The purpose of this function is to ensure that the address calling it has the right to rule on the contract.

params._disputeID: ID of the dispute in the Arbitrator contract.
params._ruling: Ruling given by the arbitrator. Note that 0 is reserved for "Not able/wanting to make a decision".

submitEvidence(bytes32,string).details: Submit a reference to evidence. EVENT.

params._evidence: A link to an evidence using its URI.

timeOutByFinder(bytes32).details: Pay finder if owner of the good fails to pay the fee.

timeOutByOwner(bytes32).details: Reimburse owner of the good if the finder fails to pay the fee.
